I now have a comprehensive understanding of the entire codebase. Let me now design the detailed implementation plan.

---

## Implementation Plan: Merging "Releases" and "Semantic Releases" into a Unified "Releases" Concept

### Summary of Current State

The codebase has two completely separate data flows in the frontend:

1. **Releases** (source-level): `releases` table, shown at `/releases` with columns Project/Provider/Repository/Version/Released/Age
2. **Semantic Releases** (project-level AI reports): `semantic_releases` table, shown at `/semantic-releases` with columns Project/Version/Status/Urgency/Age

They are connected by version string: a semantic release at `project_id + version` conceptually covers all source releases with that same version under that project. The `semantic_release_sources` join table formalizes this link.

The key challenge is that releases are **per-source** (a project can have multiple sources and multiple release records for the same version from different providers), while semantic releases are **per-project+version**. So the "Report" column on the releases table needs to look up by `(project_id, version)`.

---

### Step 1: Backend - Add Enriched Release Endpoint

**Goal**: Avoid N+1 queries on the frontend by returning releases already enriched with their semantic release status.

**File**: `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/models/release.go`

Add three new fields to the `Release` struct:

```go
// Enriched semantic release fields (populated by LEFT JOIN on semantic_releases)
SemanticReleaseID     string `json:"semantic_release_id,omitempty"`
SemanticReleaseStatus string `json:"semantic_release_status,omitempty"` // "", "pending", "processing", "completed", "failed"
SemanticReleaseUrgency string `json:"semantic_release_urgency,omitempty"` // from report JSONB
```

**File**: `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/api/pgstore.go`

Modify the three `List*Releases` methods (`ListAllReleases`, `ListReleasesBySource`, `ListReleasesByProject`) to LEFT JOIN against `semantic_releases` matching on `(project_id, version)`. The SQL change in each method adds:

```sql
LEFT JOIN LATERAL (
    SELECT sr.id, sr.status, sr.report->>'urgency' AS urgency
    FROM semantic_releases sr
    WHERE sr.project_id = p.id AND sr.version = r.version
    ORDER BY sr.created_at DESC
    LIMIT 1
) sr ON true
```

And adds three columns to the SELECT:
```sql
COALESCE(sr.id::text, ''), COALESCE(sr.status, ''), COALESCE(sr.urgency, '')
```

Then in the scan, populate the new fields:
```go
&rel.SemanticReleaseID, &rel.SemanticReleaseStatus, &rel.SemanticReleaseUrgency
```

This is the most impactful backend change. The `LATERAL` join ensures only one semantic release (latest) is returned per release row, and it adds minimal overhead since the match is on `(project_id, version)` which is an indexed combination in the semantic_releases table (there's a natural uniqueness constraint on project_id + version).

**File**: `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/api/releases.go`

No changes needed to the handler -- the store returns enriched `Release` models and the JSON serialization picks up the new fields automatically.

**No new endpoints needed.** Existing endpoints return the enriched data.

---

### Step 2: Frontend Types - Add Semantic Release Fields to Release Type

**File**: `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/web/lib/api/types.ts`

Add three optional fields to the `Release` interface (lines 76-88):

```typescript
export interface Release {
  id: string;
  source_id: string;
  version: string;
  raw_data?: Record<string, unknown>;
  released_at?: string;
  created_at: string;
  project_id?: string;
  project_name?: string;
  provider?: string;
  repository?: string;
  excluded?: boolean;
  // Enriched semantic release fields
  semantic_release_id?: string;
  semantic_release_status?: string; // "" | "pending" | "processing" | "completed" | "failed"
  semantic_release_urgency?: string;
}
```

---

### Step 3: Releases Page - Add "Report" Column

**File**: `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/web/app/releases/page.tsx`

Changes:

1. **Add imports**: Import `Sparkles`, `Loader2`, `FileText` from `lucide-react`. Import `agent` from `@/lib/api/client`.

2. **Add column header**: In the `<thead>` columns array (line 197), add `"Report"` between `"Age"` and `""` (the external link column). The array becomes:
   ```typescript
   ["Project", "Provider", "Repository", "Version", "Released", "Age", "Report", ""]
   ```

3. **Add the Report cell** in the `<tbody>` mapping, after the "Age" `<td>` (after line 318) and before the "Provider link" `<td>` (line 321). The cell renders based on `release.semantic_release_status`:

```tsx
{/* Report */}
<td className="px-4 py-3">
  {release.project_id && !release.excluded && (() => {
    const status = release.semantic_release_status;
    if (status === "completed") {
      return (
        <Link
          href={`/projects/${release.project_id}/semantic-releases/${release.semantic_release_id}`}
          className="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-[12px] font-medium hover:underline"
          style={{ color: "#2563eb" }}
          title="View report"
        >
          <FileText size={13} />
          Report
        </Link>
      );
    }
    if (status === "pending" || status === "processing") {
      return (
        <span
          className="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-[12px]"
          style={{ color: "#e8601a" }}
          title="Report generating..."
        >
          <Loader2 size={13} className="animate-spin" />
          {status}
        </span>
      );
    }
    // No semantic release exists -- show trigger button
    return (
      <button
        onClick={async () => {
          await agent.triggerRun(release.project_id!, release.version);
          // Revalidate SWR data
          mutate((key) => Array.isArray(key) && key[0]?.includes?.("releases"));
        }}
        className="inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[12px] transition-colors hover:bg-[#f3f3f1]"
        style={{ color: "#9ca3af", border: "1px solid #e8e8e5" }}
        title="Generate AI report"
      >
        <Sparkles size={13} />
      </button>
    );
  })()}
</td>
```

4. **Add SWR mutate import**: Add `mutate` to the `swr` import (already imported for data fetching, add the global `mutate` for revalidation after triggering).

5. **Add `agent` import** from `@/lib/api/client`.

**Note on `failed` status**: If `semantic_release_status === "failed"`, it falls into the "no report exists" path and shows the trigger button so the user can re-trigger. This is intentional -- a failed report should be retryable.

---

### Step 4: Projects Page - Merge the Two FlowSections

**File**: `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/web/app/projects/page.tsx`

**ProjectFlowCard changes** (lines 150-377):

1. **Remove the separate "Semantic Releases" FlowSection** (lines 293-325). Delete the entire `{srItems.length > 0 && (...)}` block.

2. **Enrich the "Releases" FlowSection** to show inline report status. Modify the release item rendering (lines 258-290) to include a small inline indicator after each version chip:

```tsx
{/* Releases flow — now with inline report indicators */}
{releases.length > 0 && (
  <FlowSection label="Releases" moreHref={`/releases?project=${project.id}`}>
    {releases.map((r) => {
      const src = sourceMap.get(r.source_id);
      // Find matching semantic release for this version
      const sr = srItems.find((s) => s.version === r.version);
      return (
        <span key={r.id} className="inline-flex items-baseline mr-2.5">
          <Link
            href={`/releases/${r.id}`}
            className={r.excluded ? "" : "text-[#2563eb] hover:underline"}
            style={{
              fontFamily: "'JetBrains Mono', monospace",
              fontSize: "12px",
              ...(r.excluded ? { color: "#c4c4c0" } : {}),
            }}
          >
            {r.version}
          </Link>
          {sr && sr.status === "completed" && (
            <Link
              href={`/projects/${project.id}/semantic-releases/${sr.id}`}
              className="ml-0.5 inline-flex items-center"
              title="View report"
            >
              <FileText size={10} style={{ color: "#2563eb" }} />
            </Link>
          )}
          {sr && (sr.status === "pending" || sr.status === "processing") && (
            <Loader2 size={10} className="ml-0.5 animate-spin" style={{ color: "#e8601a" }} />
          )}
          {src && (
            <span className="text-[11px] ml-1 hidden sm:inline" style={{ color: r.excluded ? "#dcdcda" : "#9ca3af" }}>
              ({src.repository.split("/").pop()})
            </span>
          )}
          <span className="text-[11px] ml-1" style={{ color: r.excluded ? "#dcdcda" : "#c4c4c0" }}>
            {timeAgo(r.released_at || r.created_at).replace(" ago", "")}
